{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Slot A: \"review input is scoped to the lines that changed.\" Slot B: handoff boundary (diff extraction module -> review-input builder). Slot C: if lowered to Unit, a real bug where parsed hunks are correct but wiring sends full-file content would be missed. Rejection gate: System is disqualified because this behavior can be reproduced with in-process fixtures (no real OS/network/subprocess needed); Agentic is disqualified because correctness does not depend on model output.","test_description":"Wire real local modules for diff parsing and review payload construction using a fixture PR patch containing unchanged sensitive lines plus changed lines. Assert the payload sent to the analyzer contains only changed hunks/lines and excludes unchanged file body.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Slot A: \"attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.\" Slot B: real-infra boundary (GitHub diff-position semantics over real HTTP API). Slot C: if lowered to Integration, mocked API acceptance would miss real position/side/commit mapping errors that only appear against GitHub's server rules and rendering. Rejection gate: Agentic is disqualified because this behavior checks placement mechanics, not model judgment.","test_description":"Create/use a real test PR with known changed lines, post inline comments through the automation, then query PR review comments via real GitHub API and verify each comment lands on expected file/line/side in the actual diff.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.82,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Slot A: \"identifies at least one real defect\" in a PR with known bug. Slot B: model-output boundary (quality of LLM-generated findings). Slot C: if lowered to Integration, a stubbed model can always return a canned defect and hide failure where the real model misses the bug. Rejection gate: Workflow is disqualified because this behavior focuses on a single model decision outcome (defect identification), not correctness across multiple agentic stages.","test_description":"Run analysis against a real bug-seeded PR (or fixed benchmark PR) using the real model call, repeated enough times to measure pass rate; assert at least one true-positive finding for the known bug class and no manual injection of findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.12}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to a posted inline comment ID from the same run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Slot A: \"corresponds to a posted inline comment ID from the same run.\" Slot B: handoff/state boundary (inline post results -> summary assembler). Slot C: if lowered to Unit, cross-module run-state bugs (stale IDs, mixed-run IDs) can be missed. Rejection gate: System is disqualified because this mapping invariant can be validated with in-process fakes returning realistic IDs; Agentic is disqualified because mapping does not depend on model output quality.","test_description":"Execute run orchestration with deterministic findings and a fake review-comment gateway that returns unique IDs per post; build summary and assert every summary entry references an ID that was emitted in that run and none from prior runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"No inline finding is dropped from the final summary payload before posting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Slot A: \"No inline finding is dropped from the final summary payload before posting.\" Slot B: handoff/state boundary (inline findings collection -> summary payload generator). Slot C: if lowered to Unit, end-to-end list propagation bugs (dedupe/filter/chunk logic across modules) may be missed. Rejection gate: System is disqualified because drop detection can be proven with in-process module wiring and captured payload; Agentic is disqualified because this is completeness/integrity, not model judgment.","test_description":"Run the orchestration with a fixed multi-item finding set including edge cases (same file, multiple hunks), capture the exact summary payload just before post, and assert one-to-one coverage of all inline findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The automation sequence (read diff, post inline comments, post summary) succeeds for a real pull request when provided a fixed precomputed finding set.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Slot A: \"succeeds for a real pull request\" with read/post/post sequence. Slot B: real-infra boundary (real GitHub HTTP/API behavior and sequence effects). Slot C: if lowered to Integration, mocked endpoints would miss authentication, rate-limit, ordering, and API contract failures seen only in real calls. Rejection gate: Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because findings are fixed precomputed (no model-output dependence).","test_description":"Against a live test repository PR, inject deterministic findings, execute full sequence with real API tokens, and assert all steps complete: diff retrieved, all inline comments created, summary posted, and artifacts linked to same run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.88,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full live run with model-generated findings (read diff, analyze, post inline comments, post summary) completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Slot A: \"full live run with model-generated findings ... completes correctly\" and includes read/analyze/post/post. Slot B: multi-step agentic boundary (agentic analysis decision followed by downstream actions in one pipeline). Slot C: if lowered to Agentic, you can miss failures where model output is valid in isolation but breaks later handoff/posting/summary stages in the same unattended run. Rejection gate: none; higher level not rejected because this is explicitly a full agent pipeline.","test_description":"Run the production pipeline end-to-end on a real PR with real model calls and real GitHub posting, with no human edits between stages; assert completion, inline comments posted, summary posted, and summary/comment linkage invariants hold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.72}}]}
